===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `foo2hbpl2` baraye tabdil dadan file-haye chapi (print files) ke ba dastoor foo2zjs sakhte shode-and, be shekl-e Postscript estefade mishavad. Asosan, in dastoor baraye chap ba keyfiat bala az printer-haye rangy ke foo2zjs support mikonad be kar miravad. 🌈

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-r <resolution>` --> 🎯 Ta'een-e defghat-e tasvir (resolution) baraye chap. Meslan, `-r600` defghat ra 600 DPI gharar midahad. هر چه بالاتر، کیفیت بهتر ولی حجم فایل بزرگتر.
    🔹 `-p <rang>`        --> 🎨 Ta'een-e profile rang baraye chap. Meslan, `-p "sRGB"` ya `-p "AdobeRGB"`. Agar ta'een nashavad, az profile pishfarz estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `-n <tedad>`       --> 🔢 Ta'een-e tedad copy-haye chap. Meslan, `-n 3` se copy chap mikonad.
    🔹 `| lpr`            --> 🖨️ Eefrestadan-e khorooji be printer ba dastoor lpr.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ foo2hbpl2 input.prn > output.ps

    🔹 Tabdil file `input.prn` be `output.ps`.

    $ foo2hbpl2 -r1200 input.prn | lpr

    🔹 Tabdil file `input.prn` ba defghat 1200 DPI va chap an ba lpr.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ foo2hbpl2 my_document.prn > my_document.ps

    🔹 In dastoor file `my_document.prn` ra ke az foo2zjs gerefte shode, be yek file PostScript ba name `my_document.ps` tabdil mikonad. In file PS bad az an mitavanad ba estefade az yek dastoor mesle `lpr` chap shavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `foo2hbpl2` command is used to convert print files generated by the foo2zjs driver into PostScript format. It's primarily used for high-quality printing on color printers supported by foo2zjs. 🌈

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-r <resolution>` --> 🎯 Sets the output resolution for printing. For example, `-r600` sets the resolution to 600 DPI. Higher values result in better quality but larger file sizes.
    🔹 `-p <color_profile>` --> 🎨 Specifies the color profile for printing. For example, `-p "sRGB"` or `-p "AdobeRGB"`. If not specified, the default profile is used.
    🔹 `-n <number>`     --> 🔢 Specifies the number of copies to print. For example, `-n 3` prints three copies.
    🔹 `| lpr`          --> 🖨️ Sends the output to the printer using the lpr command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ foo2hbpl2 input.prn > output.ps

    🔹 Converts the file `input.prn` to `output.ps`.

    $ foo2hbpl2 -r1200 input.prn | lpr

    🔹 Converts the file `input.prn` with a resolution of 1200 DPI and prints it using lpr.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ foo2hbpl2 my_document.prn > my_document.ps

    🔹 This command converts the file `my_document.prn`, generated from foo2zjs, into a PostScript file named `my_document.ps`. This PS file can then be printed using a command like `lpr`.

